James L. CARROLL, Percy Farrell, et al., Appellants, v. UNION SULPHUR COMPANY, a Corporation, Appellee. No. 8434. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 11, 1937. William P. Lord, of Portland, Or., for appellants. Erskine Wood, of Portland, Or., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of proctor for appellee, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed for failure of appellants to file record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
